Issue: 
Consider a scenario when a user is editing an attached document in Confluence. In this case, a notification will be generated. However, the notification message will be as followings: 
{noformat}
'user <xxx> added a file to the page <xxx>'
{noformat}

From a user’s perspective, they are editing a file and not adding/reattaching it. This will in turn confuse the user when they receive the notification as they are merely editing the file.

Suggestion:
The notification should state the following instead:
{noformat}
'user <xxx> edited a file to the page <xxx>'
{noformat}

Thank you and regards,
Lazuardi

